<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  {{> 'partials/head' }}

  <style>
    a {
      color: #1e88e5;
    }
    header {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: row;
      justify-content: space-around;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .searchBar {
      height: 16px;
      font-size: 14px;
      padding: 0.5em;
      border: none;
      outline: none;
      background: none;
    }
    .searchLine {
      border-bottom: 1px solid #d2d2d2;
    }
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, avenir next, avenir, segoe ui, helvetica neue, helvetica, Ubuntu, roboto, noto, arial, sans-serif;
    }
    h2, p {
      text-align: center;
    }
    code {
      display: block;
      padding: 0.5em;
      background-color: #f5f5f5;
      width: 50%;
      margin: 0 auto;
      word-wrap: break-word;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-family: Menlo, Consolas, Monaco, Liberation Mono, Lucida Console, monospace;
    }
    @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
      body {
        background-color: black;
        color: white;
      }
      .logo {
        filter: invert(1) hue-rotate(180deg);
      }
      .searchBar {
        color: white;
      }
      code {
        background-color: #616161;
        color: white;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <title>Error - Librarian</title>
</head>

<body>
  {{> 'partials/header' }}

  <main>
    <h2>An error occured.</h2>
    <p>You may have found a bug in Librarian. If this is a bug, open an issue on <a href="https://codeberg.org/librarian/librarian/issues/new">Codeberg</a>.</p>
    <code>{{err}}</code>
  </main>

</body>

</html>